# ðŸ“¦ Linux Package Management Cheat Sheet (RedHat vs Ubuntu)

This cheat sheet compares common package management commands side-by-side for **RedHat (RHEL/CentOS using YUM/DNF)** and **Ubuntu/Debian (APT)**.

---

## ðŸ”‘ Legend
- **RHEL/CentOS** â†’ `yum` / `dnf`  
- **Ubuntu/Debian** â†’ `apt`  

---

| Task | **RedHat (YUM/DNF)** | **Ubuntu (APT)** | Options | Description | Example |
|------|----------------------|------------------|---------|-------------|---------|
| Update package index | `yum makecache` <br> `dnf makecache` | `apt update` | `-y` â†’ auto yes | Updates local package metadata | `sudo apt update` |
| Upgrade all packages | `yum update` <br> `dnf upgrade` | `apt upgrade` | `-y` â†’ auto confirm <br> `--security` (apt) â†’ security only | Upgrades all installed packages | `sudo apt upgrade -y` |
| Full distribution upgrade | `dnf upgrade --refresh` | `apt full-upgrade` | `--refresh` â†’ refresh cache <br> `-y` â†’ auto confirm | Upgrades packages and handles dependencies (kernel, removals) | `sudo apt full-upgrade -y` |
| Install a package | `yum install pkg` <br> `dnf install pkg` | `apt install pkg` | `-y` â†’ auto confirm <br> `--downloadonly` (dnf) â†’ download only <br> `--dry-run` (apt) â†’ simulate | Installs a package | `sudo apt install nginx -y` |
| Reinstall a package | `yum reinstall pkg` <br> `dnf reinstall pkg` | `apt reinstall pkg` | `-y` â†’ auto confirm | Reinstalls a given package | `sudo apt reinstall curl` |
| Remove a package | `yum remove pkg` <br> `dnf remove pkg` | `apt remove pkg` | `-y` â†’ auto confirm | Removes package (keeps config) | `sudo apt remove nginx -y` |
| Remove pkg + config | `dnf remove pkg` | `apt purge pkg` | `-y` â†’ auto confirm | Removes package with config | `sudo apt purge nginx -y` |
| Search for a package | `yum search pkg` <br> `dnf search pkg` | `apt search pkg` | `--showduplicates` (dnf) â†’ show multiple versions | Searches repositories | `apt search apache2` |
| Show package info | `yum info pkg` <br> `dnf info pkg` | `apt show pkg` | â€” | Displays details of a package | `apt show curl` |
| List installed packages | `yum list installed` <br> `dnf list installed` | `dpkg -l` | `| grep` â†’ filter results | Shows installed packages | `dpkg -l \| grep nginx` |
| List files in package | `rpm -ql pkg` | `dpkg -L pkg` | â€” | Lists installed files of a package | `dpkg -L apache2` |
| Find which pkg owns file | `rpm -qf /path/file` | `dpkg -S /path/file` | â€” | Finds which package provides a file | `dpkg -S /bin/ls` |
| Clean cache | `yum clean all` <br> `dnf clean all` | `apt clean` <br> `apt autoclean` | `all` â†’ remove everything <br> `expire-cache` (dnf) | Removes cached packages | `sudo apt clean` |
| Remove unused deps | `yum autoremove` <br> `dnf autoremove` | `apt autoremove` | `-y` â†’ auto confirm | Removes unused dependencies | `sudo apt autoremove -y` |
| List repos | `yum repolist` <br> `dnf repolist` | `ls /etc/apt/sources.list.d/` | `all` (dnf) â†’ show all repos | Shows enabled repositories | `cat /etc/apt/sources.list` |
| Install from file | `rpm -ivh pkg.rpm` | `dpkg -i pkg.deb` | `-i` â†’ install <br> `-v` â†’ verbose <br> `-h` â†’ progress hash marks | Installs local package file | `sudo dpkg -i file.deb` |
| Fix broken deps | `yum check` <br> `dnf check` | `apt --fix-broken install` | `--fix-broken` â†’ repair | Repairs dependency issues | `sudo apt --fix-broken install` |

---

## âš¡ Notes
- RHEL 8+ prefers `dnf` (but `yum` is still an alias).  
- Ubuntu recommends `apt` for users, `apt-get` for scripts.  
- Use `-y` for automation to skip interactive prompts.  

